checkuser:
{{CheckUserForm}}
{{doc-special|CheckUser}}
In this special page, checkusers can check the IP addresses of users.
{{Identical|Check user}}

group-checkuser:
{{Cannot be the same as|group-suppress|wmf-group-patroller}}
{{doc-group|checkuser}}
check is a noun, not a verb here.

{{Identical|Check user}}

checkuser-reason:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Field name on [[Special:CheckUser]] used to detail the reason for the check. Depending on the configuration of the wiki this may or may not be required.

See screenshot of the interface '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|here]]' or above.
{{Identical|Reason}}

checkuser-users:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Radio button option on [[Special:CheckUser]] used to select the type of check that is performed. This check type gets a list of all users and IPs that have made edits for a particular IP or IP range.

See screenshot '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or above for example.

checkuser-edits:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Radio button option on [[Special:CheckUser]] used to select the type of check that is performed. This check type gets a list of all edits made by a user, IP, IP range or XFF IP.

See screenshot '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or above for example.

checkuser-ips:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Radio button option on [[Special:CheckUser]] used to select the type of check that is performed. This check type gets all IPs used by a given account.

See screenshot '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or above for example.

checkuser-period:
{{CheckUserForm}}
The label for the drop-down box shown on [[Special:CheckUser]] that allows a checkuser to filter the results to exclude results from before a defined number of days ago. Selecting 'all' (the default) does not impose this filter.

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or above for example.
{{Identical|Duration}}

checkuser-week-1:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Option to filter for results from the last week in the drop-down that is labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-period}} and shown on [[Special:CheckUser]].

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.
{{Identical|Last week}}

checkuser-week-2:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Option to filter for results from the last two weeks in the drop-down that is labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-period}} and shown on [[Special:CheckUser]].

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.

checkuser-month:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Option to filter for results from the last 30 days in the drop-down that is labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-period}} and shown on [[Special:CheckUser]].

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.

checkuser-month-2:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Option to filter for results from the last 60 days in the drop-down that is labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-period}} and shown on [[Special:CheckUser]].

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.

checkuser-all:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Option to not exclude any results based on their associated timestamp in the drop-down that is labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-period}} and shown on [[Special:CheckUser]].

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.
{{Identical|All}}

checkuser-nomatch:
Used in [[Special:CheckUser]] to indicate that no results were found with the user-supplied parameters that were submitted after pressing the button labelled by {{msg-mw|checkuser-check}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-nomatch-edits}}

checkuser-check:
{{CheckUserForm}}
Button label on [[Special:CheckUser]], where the button is used to submit the form (i.e. to run a check).

See screenshot at '[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Basic CheckUser interface]]' or the image above for an example usage.

{{Identical|Check}}

checkuser-blocked:
Used as link text in [[Special:CheckUser]] and indicates that a user or IP address is currently blocked.

The link points to [[Special:Log]] or [[Special:BlockList]] for the relevant block entry.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-gblocked}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-wasblocked}}
{{Identical|Blocked}}

checkuser-gblocked:
Used to indicate that an IP address in the results is globally blocked in [[Special:CheckUser]].

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocked}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-wasblocked}}

checkuser-wasblocked:
Used as link text in [[Special:CheckUser]] as extra information indicating that the user was blocked at some point in time. The link points to [[Special:Log]] for the last block entry affecting the user. See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocked}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-gblocked}}

checkuser-massblock:
{{CheckUserGetUsersBlockForm}}
Used as fieldset label for the checkuser mass block form shown in [[Special:CheckUser]] when results have been loaded for the 'get actions' check type.

This message is followed by the following message:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-massblock-text}}
{{Identical|Block selected users}}

checkuser-blockemail:
[[File:Checkuser - get users - 2020-05-29.png|thumb|Checkuser interface]]
Used as a label for a checkbox asking to block email access.

Appears as part of a list with these messages:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag-talk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktalk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blockemail}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-reblock}}

checkuser-blocktalk:
Used as a label for a checkbox asking to block talk page access.
[[File:Checkuser - get users - 2020-05-29.png|thumb|Checkuser interface]]
Appears as part of a list with these messages:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag-talk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktalk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blockemail}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-reblock}}

checkuser-blocktag:
{{CheckUserGetUsersBlockForm}}
Used as checkbox label in [[Special:CheckUser]].

This message is followed by "tag" input box. The input box is for text which replaces the entire wikitext of the concerned page.

Appears as part of a list with these messages:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag-talk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktalk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blockemail}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-reblock}}

checkuser-blocktag-talk:
{{CheckUserGetUsersBlockForm}}
Used as checkbox label in [[Special:CheckUser]].

This message is followed by "talktag" input box. The input box is for text which replaces the entire wikitext of the concerned page.

Appears as part of a list with these messages:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag-talk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktalk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blockemail}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-reblock}}

checkuser-reblock:
{{CheckUserGetUsersBlockForm}}
Used as checkbox label in [[Special:CheckUser]].

This message is followed by "talktag" input box. The input box is for text which replaces the entire wikitext of the concerned page.

Appears as part of a list with these messages:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktag-talk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blocktalk}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-blockemail}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-reblock}}

checkuser-massblock-commit:
{{CheckUserGetUsersBlockForm}}
Used as submit button text in [[Special:CheckUser]] for the form {{msg-mw|checkuser-massblock}}.
{{Identical|Block selected users}}

checkuser-block-success:
Used as success message in [[Special:CheckUser]] for the form {{msg-mw|checkuser-massblock}}.

Parameters:
* $1 - a list of one or more usernames
* $2 - the number of usernames in <code>$1</code>

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-failure}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-limit}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-noreason}}

checkuser-block-failure:
Used as failure message in [[Special:CheckUser]] for the form {{msg-mw|checkuser-massblock}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-success}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-limit}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-noreason}}

checkuser-block-limit:
Used as failure message in [[Special:CheckUser]] for the form {{msg-mw|checkuser-massblock}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-success}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-failure}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-noreason}}

checkuser-block-noreason:
Used as failure message in [[Special:CheckUser]] for the form {{msg-mw|checkuser-massblock}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-success}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-failure}}
* {{msg-mw|Checkuser-block-limit}}

checkuser-search-submit:
{{CheckUserLogForm}}
Submit button for the form shown on [[Special:CheckUserLog]] to refine the log of checks performed by checkusers. See screenshot "[[mw:Extension:CheckUser#Basic_interface|Example log]]".
{{Identical|Search}}

checkuser-log-search-target:
{{CheckUserLogForm}}
Label of form field on [[Special:CheckUserLog]]'s search form. Valid values in the field can be either an IP address, an IP address range or a username.
{{Identical|Target}}

checkuser-log-search-initiator:
{{CheckUserLogForm}}
Label of form field on [[Special:CheckUserLog]]'s search form. Valid values in the field can be a username.

The word "Initiator" should be the same as in {{msg-mw|checkuser-log-search-initiator}} without the colon.

{{Identical|Initiator}}

checkuser-userlinks-ip:
{{notranslate}}
Links shown next to an IP address in a CheckUser result entry. $1 - IP address

See also:
*{{msg-mw|Signature}}
*{{msg-mw|Checkuser-userlinks}}

checkuser-investigateblock-reason:
{{InvestigateBlockForm}}
Label for a text input in the [[Special:InvestigateBlock]] form
{{identical|Reason}}

checkuser-investigate-preliminary-notice:
Message shown if an investigation involves an IP address.

"Account information" is {{msg-mw|Checkuser-investigate-tab-preliminary-check}}

"IPs & User agents" is {{msg-mw|Checkuser-investigate-tab-compare}}

checkuser-investigate-preliminary-table-:
Label for a table header in [[Special:Investigate]]. Means "the day on which (the account) was attached".

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Centralauth-admin-list-attached-on}}

checkuser-investigate-compare-toollinks-:
{{optional}}
WHOIS/RDNS tool link. Label for an option in a dropdown list.

See also {{msg-mw|checkuser-investigate-compare-toollinks}}
